{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Glalie}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ice|prevnum=361|prev=Snorunt|nextnum=363|next=Spheal|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Glalie}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Glalie\n|jname=オニゴーリ\n|jtranslit=Onigōri\n|tmname=Onigohri\n|forme=2\n|form2=Mega Glalie\n|image2=362Glalie-Mega.png\n|mega=Glalitite\n|ndex=362\n|hdex=172\n|hdex6=180\n|sdex=207\n|adex=247\n|fbrow=175\n|abrow=214\n|type1=Ice\n|category=Face\n|height-ftin=4\'11"\n|height-m=1.5\n|weight-lbs=565.5\n|weight-kg=256.5\n|height-ftin2=6\'11"\n|height-m2=2.1\n|weight-lbs2=772.1\n|weight-kg2=350.2\n|color=Gray\n|abilityn=dm\n|abilitylayout=2+1\n|abilitycolm=2\n|ability1=Inner Focus\n|ability2=Ice Body\n|abilityd=Moody\n|abilitym=Refrigerate\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Fairy\n|egggroup2=Mineral\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evhp=2\n|expyield=168\n|oldexp=187\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|catchrate=75\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=glalie\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Glalie\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'オニゴーリ\'\'\' \'\'Onigohri\'\') is an {{type|Ice}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Snorunt}} starting at [[level]] 42. It is one of Snorunt\'s final forms, the other being {{p|Froslass}}. It can [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]] into \'\'\'Mega Glalie\'\'\' using the [[Glalitite]].\n\n==Biology==\nGlalie is a spherical Pokémon that consists of a black rock core covered by ice. The icy covering has several holes and spaces across this Pokémon\'s body. Blue eyes and a mouth with flat teeth are visible through three of these holes. There are two large, black, conical horns on either side of Glalie\'s head.\n\nMega Glalie\'s jaw is dislocated because of the overwhelming energy, causing its mouth to extend to the length of its face. The lower jaw is all black except for two light-blue, conical, icy spikes. The pupils in Mega Glalie\'s eyes are now red instead of black. The horns on top Mega Glalie\'s head have been partially turned into ice, with the addition of a third horn on its forehead.\n\nGlalie\'s icy body is actually rock that is not particularly hard. It does not melt, and it can control ice by instantly freezing moisture in the air into any desirable shape. This ability is used to drape itself in ice armor and freeze its prey, which it then consumes whole. It prefers consuming Pokémon like {{p|Vanillite}} that are already frozen though. It can be found in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Cave Pokémon|caves}}, particularly when the outside weather lacks snow. Mega Glalie can spill endless blizzards from its broken mouth, though it gets irritated by the fact that it can no longer consume its prey.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Mount Lanakila Glalie.png|thumb|220px|left|Glalie in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:M19 Mega Glalie.png|thumb|220px|left|Mega Glalie in the anime]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Ash\'s Glalie]]=====\n{{Ash}}\'s {{p|Snorunt}} evolved into {{AP|Glalie}} in \'\'[[AG123|Rhapsody in Drew]]\'\'. It only stayed during the [[Ever Grande Conference]]. It is now residing at {{an|Professor Oak}}\'s [[Professor Oak\'s Laboratory|lab]].\n\n=====Other=====\nA Glalie appeared in \'\'[[DP116|The Drifting Snorunt!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{OBP|Poacher|DP116}}. The poacher used Glalie to assist in capturing a Snorunt, which it did by frightening it into submission. However, it was defeated by [[Ash\'s Chimchar]] and a {{pkmn2|wild}} {{p|Froslass}}.\n\nA Glalie appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW140|Survival of the Striaton Gym!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Morana]]. It was seen battling and defeating [[Cress\'s Panpour]].\n\nA Glalie that can [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]] appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\', under the control of [[Levi]]\'s Mega Wave. Glalie was used to battle against {{OBP|Volcanion|M19}}. It was later freed from Levi\'s control when [[Alva]]\'s Mega Wave Crystal was destroyed, and it escaped.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Glalie appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M08|Lucario and the Mystery of Mew]]\'\'.\n\nA Glalie made a brief cameo in \'\'[[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky - Beyond Time & Darkness]]\'\'.\n\nA Glalie that can [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]] into Mega Glalie appeared in the ending segment of \'\'[[XYS02|Mega Evolution Special II]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Glalie appeared in \'\'[[SM060|Getting a Jump on the Competition!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the [[Pokémon Sled Jump Games]].\n\nA wild Glalie appeared in \'\'[[SM126|Pikachu\'s Exciting Adventure!]]\'\', where it flew past Ash\'s Pokémon while they were sliding down [[Mount Lanakila]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG123|Glalie|Ash\'s Pokédex|Glalie, the Face Pokémon. Glalie has a tempered ice body that doesn\'t melt even under a direct flame. It can freeze vapors in the air instantly.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP116|Glalie|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Glalie, the Face Pokémon and an evolved form of {{p|Snorunt}}. Glalie protects itself by creating ice armor from airborne moisture.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer===\n[[File:Mega Glalie ORAS Trailer.png|thumb|250px|Mega Glalie in the animated trailer]]\nA [[Mega Evolution|Mega]] Glalie made a cameo appearance in the [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Pokémon Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer]], where it was seen battling a Mega {{p|Steelix}}.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Noland Glalie Adventures.png|thumb|150px|Glalie in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Ash & Pikachu manga===\n{{main|Ash\'s Glalie}}\n{{Ash}} owns a Glalie in [[Ash & Pikachu]] just like his anime counterpart.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn \'\'[[PS251|The Beginning of the End with Kyogre & Groudon XIII]]\'\', [[Glacia]] of the [[Hoenn]] [[Elite Four]] was seen in possession of a Glalie.\n\n{{FB|Factory Head|Noland}} was seen picking a Glalie as one of his [[rental Pokémon]] in his {{pkmn|battle}} against {{adv|Emerald}} in \'\'[[PS307|Gotcha Where I Wantcha, Glalie]]\'\'. Although he came close to winning by delivering a would-be-fatal {{m|Sheer Cold}} that succeeded in hitting his target, [[Emerald\'s Sceptile]] was in fact, unbeknownst to both Noland and Emerald, not meant to be a rental Pokémon and survived due to his higher level. He eventually lost to Sceptile\'s {{m|Iron Tail}}, allowing Emerald to win the [[Symbol|Knowledge Symbol]].\n\nThe {{gdis|Battle Factory|III}} rented a Glalie, which was stolen by [[Guile Hideout]] in \'\'[[PS315|Skirting Around Surskit I]]\'\'.\n\nA Glalie appeared in the {{chap|Sun, Moon, Ultra Sun & Ultra Moon}}<!--[[PASM32]]-->, where it was seen on [[Mount Lanakila]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Battle Frontier manga===\nA Glalie appeared in \'\'[[CBF1|Enta Arrives at the Battle Frontier!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\nA Glalie appeared in \'\'[[PNA4|The Scarlet Scroll: Kunoichi\'s Situation]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Glalie (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n====Glalie====\n{{Dex/Header|type=Ice}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=172|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Glalie has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its foe solid. After immobilizing its foe in ice, this Pokémon enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=A 